	<method name="POST" id="rebuildServer">
		<wadl:doc xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:lang="EN" title="Rebuild specified server">
			<para role="shortdesc">Rebuild the specified server.</para>
			<para>The rebuild operation removes all data on the server and replaces it with the specified image. The serverID
				and all IP addresses remain the same. If you specify name, metadata, accessIPv4, or accessIPv6 in the rebuild
				request, new values replace existing values. Otherwise, these values do not change. You can inject data into
				the file system during the rebuild.</para>
			<note>
				<para>This operation is not available for OnMetal servers.</para>
			</note>
			<para>Specify the target server ID in the URI.</para>
			<para>In the request body, specify the rebuild action followed by various attributes, listed in the following
				parameters section.</para>
		</wadl:doc>
		<request>
			<representation mediaType="application/json">
				<wadl:doc xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:lang="EN">
